---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'StackAdapt ChatGPT ads: prompt-based targeting at $15-60 CPM';
const description = 'DSP 平台 StackAdapt 泄露的资料显示，ChatGPT 广告基于用户提示词的相关性进行投放，CPM 价格 $15-$60，试点项目最低预算 $50,000。';
---

<Layout 
  title={title}
  description={description}
  type="article"
  publishedTime="2026-04-21"
  tags={["OpenAI", "ChatGPT", "AI-Advertising", "Agent-Economy", "Monetization"]}
>
  <article class="article-content">
    <h1 class="lang-content lang-zh active">StackAdapt 在 ChatGPT 投放广告：基于提示词匹配，CPM $15-60</h1>
    <h1 class="lang-content lang-en">StackAdapt ChatGPT ads: prompt-based targeting at $15-60 CPM</h1>
    
    <time datetime="2026-04-21">2026-04-21</time>
    
    <div class="lang-content lang-zh active">
      <p>据 Adweek 独家报道，程序化广告平台 StackAdapt 的内部资料泄露，揭示了 ChatGPT 广告试点项目的详细运作方式。</p>
      <p><strong>核心要点：</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>投放机制</strong>：基于用户输入提示词的语义相关性匹配广告，而非传统的人口统计学定向</li>
        <li><strong>定价模式</strong>：CPM（千次展示成本）$15-$60，远高于传统展示广告</li>
        <li><strong>准入门槛</strong>：试点项目最低预算 $50,000，筛选大型广告主优先测试</li>
        <li><strong>独家合作</strong>：StackAdapt 作为首批接入 ChatGPT 广告生态的 DSP 之一</li>
      </ul>
      <p>这一模式标志着广告行业从"搜索意图"向"对话意图"的范式转移。当用户在 ChatGPT 中提问时，AI 分析其需求意图并实时匹配相关广告——这比关键词搜索更能捕捉用户的真实需求场景。</p>
      <p>对于广告主而言，这意味着可以介入用户决策的更早期阶段；对于 OpenAI，这是将海量对话流量商业化的关键一步；而对于整个 AI 行业，这可能是"Agent 经济"中广告模式的原型。</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.adweek.com/media/exclusive-leaked-deck-reveals-stackadapts-playbook-for-chatgpt-ads/" target="_blank">阅读原文</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="lang-content lang-en">
      <p>Adweek's exclusive report reveals leaked internal documents from programmatic advertising platform StackAdapt, detailing how ChatGPT's ad pilot program operates.</p>
      <p><strong>Key highlights:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Targeting mechanism</strong>: Ads matched based on semantic relevance to user prompts, not traditional demographic targeting</li>
        <li><strong>Pricing model</strong>: CPM (cost per thousand impressions) ranges from $15-$60, significantly higher than traditional display ads</li>
        <li><strong>Entry barrier</strong>: $50,000 minimum spend for the pilot program, prioritizing large advertisers for initial testing</li>
        <li><strong>Exclusive partnership</strong>: StackAdapt as one of the first DSPs integrated into ChatGPT's advertising ecosystem</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This model marks a paradigm shift in advertising from "search intent" to "conversation intent." When users ask questions in ChatGPT, the AI analyzes their needs and matches relevant ads in real-time—capturing user intent more precisely than keyword searches.</p>
      <p>For advertisers, this means engaging at earlier stages of user decision-making; for OpenAI, it's a crucial step toward monetizing massive conversational traffic; and for the AI industry, this could be the prototype for advertising models in the "Agent Economy."</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.adweek.com/media/exclusive-leaked-deck-reveals-stackadapts-playbook-for-chatgpt-ads/" target="_blank">Read the full article</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to articles</a>
  </article>
</Layout>
